Trump renames Department of Defense the 'Department of War'
description: The US president will sign an executive order permitting use of the Department of War as a 'secondary title' for the sprawling department, a White House document said, apparently due to its official name being set in law. Trump in recent weeks has said that he wanted to make such a shift, claiming the department's title was too 'defensive.'

headline: NATO: Europe is caught in Trump's 'protection racket'
description: The Europeans, eager to keep the US from abandoning Ukraine, waver between submission and emancipation. Yet for Trump, who doesn't heed political or moral arguments, NATO must, above all, pay off, writes Le Monde columnist Alain Frachon.

headline: Giorgio Armani, one of the makers of modern fashion, is dead
description: Creator, designer and stylist, he made the tailored suit into a status symbol. Armani, who reigned for more than 40 years over a veritable empire, died on Thursday, September 4, at the age of 91, his fashion house confirmed.

headline: Sakurajima: Life in the shadow of the Japanese monster
description: 'Of Volcanoes and Men' (5/6). In southern Japan, Kagoshima's residents live under the constant threat of Sakurajima, one of the most active volcanoes in the archipelago. Photographer Chikashi Suzuki observed the city, with both fear and reverence, prepare for the volcano's next eruption.

headline: French budget minister: 'France cannot go an entire year without a budget'
description: With the French government at risk of collapsing, Amélie de Montchalin says in an interview that the deadline to submit a draft budget to the Assemblée Nationale is October 13. Any later and a special law would be required to avoid a shutdown, which she sees as a problematic last resort.

description: The recipe for this comforting pastry, enjoyed as a snack or at breakfast? Croissant dough, vanilla custard and chocolate chips. Here is our selection of bakeries offering the best versions.
